                  </hi>. I am a window. On the evening of the 6th of Feb<lb></lb>ruary 1836, I was at the prisoner's house—I used to work for his wife—he came in that evening, pulled off his great coat and watch, and left them at home.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> It is false, it is very easy to get a story like this—the prosecutor, policeman, and witness, and witness have ben together somje time—this witness was with Julians Simms last Fewbruary twlemoth. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I have not agreed with Simms to say any things—I know nothing about her—I have to come here when she was in troble, and have seen her since but have had no correspoduce with her.</p>
